llows readers to discover the innovative ways poets translate "melody," "dynamics," "tempo," "mood," and other musical elements into literal and figurative expressions that invite readers to imagine the music in their mind's eye (i.e., their mind's ear).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aPoetryxHistory and criticism. 4aAmerican Literature. 4aAmerikanische Literatur. 4aCognitive Poetics. 4aIntermediality. 4aIntermedialität. 4aJazz Music. 4aJazz-Musik. 4aKognitive Poetik. 70(DE-601)1062786140(DE-588)4028532-7aJazz2gnd 70(DE-601)2548730490(DE-588)4530403-8aJazz poetry2gnd 70(DE-601)3262701670(DE-588)4605581-2aIntermedialität2gnd 70(DE-601)6004440900(DE-588)7663434-6aKognitive Poetik2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831103952800 cprintz978311032654340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110339017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110339017.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017